Resource.Description: Action List Extension adds a customizable report to the interface that allows the display and manipulation of multiple items from one location.

Resource.Name: Expand All
Resource.Description: This Form Extension adds a dropdown menu to a transition form that allows the user to quickly expand certain or all expanders. When an option is selected, the user will also be redirected to the particular expander chosen.

Resource.Name: Transition Icon
Resource.Description: This Form Extension adds an icon to a transition form that allows the user to quickly identify the current application in use.

Field.Name: Comments
Field.Description: General comments that relate to this CR, to be retained as part of the record

Field.Name: Work Log
Field.Description: Remarks between the developers/software providers, to be maintained at the discretion of the vendor team

Field.Name: Item Id
Field.Description: The displayed identifier of the item

Field.Name: CM Team Acceptance
Field.Description: Used only by CM Team to mark a Change Request as ready for the Government to review and decide whether the vendor may being work

Field.Name: RM Team Acceptance
Field.Description: Used only by RM Team to signify a CR's requirements are properly identified

Field.Name: Title/Summary
Field.Description: High-level summary of the change being requested, expressed clearly enough for non-technical staff to comprehend

Field.Name: Description
Field.Description: Detailed description of the change being requested, specifying affected components/subsystems, and to what degree items will be changed

Field.Name: Justification
Field.Description: Justification for requesting the change and consequences of not performing it

Field.Name: Requirement Statement/User Story
Field.Description: The applicable requirement statement or user story addressed by the CR

Field.Name: Acceptance Criteria
Field.Description: Any specific test or evaluation to be followed in confirming the success of the change

Field.Name: Requirements Number
Field.Description: Reference number from the related requirements tracking system

Field.Name: Version Found in
Field.Description: Version number of the SDD Application in which the issue/defect was discovered

Field.Name: T&E Notification Memo
Field.Description: Boilerplate text to be used in generating test results for this CR

Field.Name: T&E Notification Number
Field.Description: A number to be assigned to the test effort for this CR

Field.Name: Priority
Field.Description: The product team's rating of its urgency to accomplish the change (1 = High, 5= Low)

Field.Name: Version Fixed In
Field.Description: Planned version number of the SDD application in which the issue/defect will be fixed

Field.Name: SDD Application Module(s)
Field.Description: An optional subcomponent of the SDD Application, if so used by the product team

Field.Name: Related Tracking System
Field.Description: Selection of a listed tracking system in which the CR originated, if applicable

Field.Name: Related Tracking Number
Field.Description: Tracking system's specific ticket number for the CR, if applicable

Field.Name: SDD Application
Field.Description: Selection of SDD application being changed

Field.Name: Severity
Field.Description: The degree of impact on the product or system if the requested change is not made ( 1=Emergency, 2= Urgent, 3= High, 4= Routine, 5=Minor)

Field.Name: Change Type
Field.Description: Selection of approach requested to accomplish the change (Change code or the DB schema, Data Table Update, Change to Configuration)

Field.Name: Issue Type
Field.Description: Selection of issue type that made the change request necessary (Defect/SIR, SCR-T, or SCR-F)

Field.Name: Discretionary
Field.Description: Indication that the effort is discretionary or if it is mandatory, based on SDD guidance

Field.Name: Story Points
Field.Description: Rate of effort of work in a Fibonacci numerical sequence to be used by Product Team at their discretion.

Field.Name: Release Qualification
Field.Description: Degree of impact on the SDD Application's baseline if the if the change described in the CR were to be implemented by itself

Field.Name: Date of Gov't Approval
Field.Description: Auto populated based on exact date Gov't approved the CR

Field.Name: Date of Deployment
Field.Description: Auto populated based on CP Planned or targeted date for deployment of the change described in the Change Request

Field.Name: Process Deviation
Field.Description: Used only by CM Team to document deviations from the standard process

Field.Name: Branch/PMO
Field.Description: SDD Branch/PMO managing the application

Field.Name: Tag/Label
Field.Description: Optional categorical words to be applied to the CR record, for later use by the product team
